Original Parkside Charmer

On a corner location, with park views, this is a wonderful opportunity not to be missed close to Coburg High School, Merri Creek Trail, Shops & Public Transport.

Description:
AMAZING NORTH FACING BALCONY
There is no doubt that this huge north facing balcony adds that special little touch to this stylish one bedroom apartment. Positioned high on the 5th floor with stunning panoramic views, this light filled apartment provides the perfect entry point into the Melbourne market. Beautiful presentation matches the finish featuring open plan living zone with tiled floors, kitchen with stone bench tops, glass splash backs and a generous amount of storage space. The bedroom provides natural light and BIR's. Enjoy the classy finishes and huge mirrored splash back the bathroom offers. Other features include, ceiling fan, heating, cooling, secure entrance, supermarket on ground floor of building and secure car park. Step onto the tram which passes your doorstep and travel only 5km to the University of Melbourne or 6.5Km into the heart of Melbournes CBD. You may also prefer to stay closer to home and enjoy the popular local pubs, cafes, restaurants and retail stores in and around Coburg and Brunswick.

Description:
Contemporary Perks
Modern living is hard to resist in this sleek two bedroom apartment enjoying the benefits of a lively locale with trams, cafes, Campbell Reserve, a gym and supermarket practically on the doorstep. Featuring flowing open design and a northerly balcony showcasing amazing views, it's finished with stainless steel Fisher & Paykel appliances, highlighting a gas cooktop with wok burner and fan forced electric oven, and elegant touches including stone surfaces. Bedrooms host fitted built-in robes, a central bathroom with European laundry is poised between them, and heating, a secure entrance, elevator access and allocated garage parking ensure overall appeal. Close to the Merri Creek Trail and minutes from the vibrant centre of the city, the living is easy.

Description:
Heritage Classic with Potential!
Ideally located in one of the quiet streets of Coburg surrounded by other vintage gems, this semi-detached brick beauty on a corner block presents a terrific lifestyle opportunity with plenty of scope to enhance and plenty of room to expand (STCA). The interior comprises two double bedrooms (master with large BIRs) and central bathroom, front lounge and kitchen/meals area with gas cooker through to the sunroom. Add to this a split-system a/c, laundry and separate WC, plus undercover patio, garage and sizeable north-west facing backyard. Quiet and incredibly convenient, it's walking distance to Merri Creek trails and parkland, Murray Road/Elizabeth Street buses, close to Coburg Hill Shopping Centre, Newland Primary School and Coburg High School. What an opportunity!

Classic Style with Instant Appeal
Freestanding and fabulous, this distinctive period home is sure to impress with its surprisingly spacious floorplan, generous land size and exclusive location just north of Brunswick's border. Quality features with plenty of scope to further enhance, the home's delightful interior comprises two generous bedrooms (one with BIRs) and gorgeous period-inspired bathroom complete with clawfoot bath. Add to this a wide loungeroom with pressed-metal ceilings (potential third bedroom), study, open dining area and adjoining kitchen. Other highlights include ducted heating, solid timber floors, high ceilings, internal laundry, plus a north-facing backyard garden and front carport via gated driveway. Ideally situated in one of the area's premier pockets, it's close to Nicholson Street/Moreland Road trams, primary and secondary schools, easy access to Moreland Station, Sydney Road shops, cafes and restaurants. Modern conveniences include a separate laundry, split system heating/cooling, secure entry, lift access and secure car space plus storage unit that assure comfort and security. A short walk delivers the varied cafes, restaurants and specialty shopping of Sydney Road, trams, Coburg Station, choice of schools and Farmers Markets that together with direct access to Merri Creek parklands and trails makes this apartment one not to miss.

Lovingly maintained by the one owner for 37 years, this freestanding three bedroom residence set on approximately 420m2 of level grounds, boasts excellent city convenience in an exclusive Coburg pocket. A quaint and welcoming front yard with convenient side driveway paves the way to the generously proportioned home, newly carpeted and painted for fresh appeal. Large L-shaped lounge/dining wraps to kitchen/meals with 900mm 5 burner gas cooker and oven/grill, with entertaining extending to rear yard undercover alfresco area. Voluptuous king-sized bedrooms enjoy use of bathroom with separate bath and shower, plus there is an internal laundry for convenience. This is a unique property in great condition with the bonus of huge potential to personalise and glamorise, with dual access single garage offering potential to reinstate rear ROW. Includes two reverse cycle air conditioners, wall mounted air-con, ducted heating, CCTV security, alarm, shed. Close to Sydney Road shops, cafes, transport, Moreland Station, childcare facilities, Nicholson Street, primary and secondary schools, Coburg shopping precinct, Merri Creek trails and parklands.
Insights: 111 The Avenue, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Expansive Apartment In A Prime Coburg Locale
Enjoying all the advantages of a prime Coburg location, this spacious two bedroom apartment offers exciting entry to this cosmopolitan locale. Exuding a stylish architectural features including modern panelled windows and polished timber floors, this fashionable apartment boasts expansive living, thoughtfully zoned for dining and lounging, and opening to a privately screened balcony for relaxed indoor/outdoor living. A stylishly appointed high-end kitchen boasting granite benchtops, glass splashbacks and electric cooking including an impressive 900mm oven and dishwasher will have the keenest of cooks in foodie heaven, and also provides an attractive point of interest in this inviting living space. Tucked at the rear, two privately zoned bedrooms with BIR's share a spacious bathroom with stone topped vanity that incorporates convenient laundry facilities, plus a secure entry and underground car space, split system heating/cooling and storage cage enhance appeal. Boasting immediate access to Coburg Lake and within easy reach of vibrant Sydney Road shopping and cafes, transport including Batman Station, Coburg Olympic Pool and the Leisure Centre.

Description:
Under Offer
Period Prize in a Sought-After Locale. With its original elegance, versatile floorplan and delightful garden surrounds, this captivating Californian delivers a family lifestyle of quality and class in an exclusive Coburg pocket - moments from Merri Creek trails and parkland. Immaculate interior comprises three double bedrooms and central bathroom, spacious lounge and dining through to the updated kitchen/meals with Blanco cooking appliances and dishwasher. Add to this heating and cooling, new wool-based wall insulation, solid timber floors, laundry and second WC, front off-street parking, plus undercover decking, established backyard garden with plenty of room to expand in the future (STCA). Easy access to a range of lifestyle attractions including local cafes and popular schools, endless array of restaurants, shops and supermarkets, as well as a choice of tramlines to university/hospital precincts and the CBD. Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
There Is So Much To Love
Nestled in the heart of West Coburg on a delightfully private 408 square metre parcel of land, this gorgeous home boasts a flexible floor plan and is immediately comfortable, with scope to further extend.
The property features:
Four main rooms off the wide entrance hall
Open plan kitchen and casual living
Central bathroom
Outside laundry and second toilet
Side drive to garage
All this situated within close, easy reach of Moreland Train Station, tram, parkland, schools and the local shopping hub.
There is so much to love in this charming home, whether it's the fantastic blend of past and present or the tranquil garden at the rear, it's a must see this weekend.
This property is on the market and will be sold.
Call Andrew Pennisi anytime for more details or drop in to one of our advertised viewings.

Spacious Retro Apartment with Great Scope to Refresh
Delightful character filled unit amongst a leafy apartment block comprising 2 generous bedrooms, original kitchen, oversized meals / living area, separate laundry, bathroom with shower over bath and a cute balcony overlooking picturesque trees and greenery.
With secure undercover parking and located close to Merri Creek trails / parklands and Nicholson Street tram-line just a stroll away whether you are nesting or investing this unique unit will appeal to all.
